<p>July 1915</p>
<p>Thursday 1</p>
<p>Reached Brisbane &amp; had tea at [indecipherable] with Fothergill &amp; Johnson [late of R.N.] whom we picked up at Murwillumbah.</p>
<p>Met De Lacey &amp; Saunders &amp; had a glass of port wine with them.</p>
<p>De Lacey informed me that promotions are out. Thinks I am good for a corporal &amp; raises my spirits, only for a time however.</p>
<p>Arrived at camp I find Clarke will probable be last Corporal &amp; I have been passed over</p>
<p>Depressed &amp; dreary</p>
